Windows 10 Build 16215 is out

Microsoft today released yet another Windows 10 Insider Preview version. Windows 10 build 16215 which represents the upcoming Windows 10 Fall Creators Update, code name "Redstone 3", is available now for Fast Ring Insiders. This build comes with a number of changes:

This build introduces new UI for Start and Action Center that includes elements of our new Fluent Design System which was announced at Build 2017.

Windows 10 build 16215 feature a lot of other settings. You can learn about them from the official change log. Improvements were made for Settings, Windows Update, Game Bar, Bash on Ubuntu (Windows Subsystem for Linux), Ease of Access, Hyper-V
